The nature and influences of customer behaviour. User experience design - idea development. The person and his needs. Problem analysis and value. User experience testing options. User experience audit.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course aims to develop the ability to use different design methods to influence the user experience in real and virtual environments.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student: 1) knows the mechanisms and factors of user experience development; 2) is able to analyse the user experience of the product/service comprehensively; 3) knows the specifics of the development of the user experience in a virtual environment; 4) is able to prepare a project plan for user experience analysis and carry out a user experience survey and develop improvement proposals based on it.
